ActOther Than Statutory Authority
SubjectConfirmation of Palling Indian Reserve No. 1
PrecisOrder (1) confirming that the DECKER LAKE INDIAN RESERVE NO. 10A, now part of Palling Indian Reserve No. 1, consisting of 8.540 hectares (21.10 acres) of land (Parcel 1) was set apart as reserve on February 5, 1930 and continues to be set apart as reserve for the Wet’suwet’en First Nation; and (2) setting apart 0.766 hectare (1.893 acres) of land (Parcel 2), for the use and benefit of the Wet’suwet’en First Nation as an addition to PALLING INDIAN RESERVE NO. 1. Both parcels of land are located in the Regional District of Bulkley-Nechako at approximately 20 kilometres from the village of Burns Lake, British Columbia.
